# Z-Axis Depth Detection Plan

## Goal Description
Switch the "click" mechanism from detecting finger curl (angle) to detecting a "poke" motion (Z-axis depth) where the fingertip moves significantly in front of the wrist.

## User Review Required
None.

## Proposed Changes
### files
#### [MODIFY] [app.py](file:///Users/aniruddhmodi/Documents/PycharmProjects/AirPlay/app.py)
- **Parameters**:
    - Add `DEPTH_THRESHOLD = 0.15` (Start value, may need tuning).
    - Add `DEPTH_RELEASE_THRESHOLD` (for debounce/hysteresis, maybe 0.10).
- **Logic**:
    - Get `wrist` landmark (index 0).
    - Calculate `z_diff = wrist.z - tip.z` for each finger.
    - **State Machine**:
        - `UP` -> `DOWN`: if `z_diff > DEPTH_THRESHOLD`.
        - `DOWN` -> `UP`: if `z_diff < DEPTH_RELEASE_THRESHOLD`.
- **Debug**:
    - Display `z_diff` (formatted, e.g., `0.12`) near the finger instead of the angle.

## Verification Plan
### Manual Verification
- Run the app.
- Poke towards the camera.
- Verify "Pressed" state triggers when pushing forward.
- Verify "Released" state triggers when pulling back.
